# CSS

**Layout / tokens**

1. Nest (`.parent { .child {} }`); short inner names when scoped by parent.
2. Colors/spacing/size from **`scales.css` / `tokens.css` / `tokens-node-editor.css`**; new token only if ≥2 uses, JS‑consumed, or semantic — otherwise comment one-offs.
3. Role: node editor **`tokens-node-editor.css`**; DOM UI **`tokens.css`**; primitives **`scales.css`**.
4. Disabled UI: **`--opacity-disabled`** — not raw `opacity: 0.5`.
5. **No `cursor: pointer` by default** — `default` on click targets unless resize/drag cues apply.

**Classes:** kebab-case; nested names stay short (**no BEM** `__`/`--`). Modifiers: `.foo.is-active`, `.button.primary`.

**Global (`src/styles/`)** vs **Svelte `<style>`:** globals for cross-cutting layout/tokens; colocate owned component styles.

**Motion:** Honor **`prefers-reduced-motion`** (`src/styles/reduced-motion.css` + scoped media / zero-duration transitions).

**Format:** 2 spaces; layout → box → visual → typography; section comments on large blocks.

Stylelint absent — honor this doc + ESLint-Svelte during review.

```css
.bottom-bar {
  .section {
    .play-button { width: var(--size-xl); }
  }
}
```
